text: Musninkai is a town in Širvintos district municipality, Vilnius County, east Lithuania. According to the Lithuanian census of 2011, the town has a population of 415 people. The town has a Catholic church. Its alternate names include Muśniki (Polish), Musnikų, Musninkay, Musninkų, and Musnik (Yiddish).United States Board on Geographic Names - Musninkai.
